---
import { site } from "../data/site";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title={`About — ${site.name}`} description={`About ${site.name}.`}>
  <h1 class="font-serif mb-10">About</h1>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <p>
      I'm a software engineer with around three years of professional experience, mostly building
      web applications in C# and JavaScript or one of its many cousins.
    </p>
    <p>
      I got into web development back when I was running a small business and got tired of answering
      the same customer questions and sharing Excel files for stock and orders. I had learned a bit
      of programming in college, so I tried to use such skills to publish a FAQ page.
    </p>
    <p>
      Since then I've shipped production systems used by thousands of people and internal tools used
      by nobody but me. I’ve worked across the stack in small teams, taking full ownership of
      projects from conception to delivery. So I'm familiar with working in both legacy systems and
      highly sophisticated (and usually overly-complex) corporate architectures.
    </p>
    <p>
      To me, writing software is more than just code, it's a craft. I care about what I build,
      striving for simplicity, correctness, and a touch of elegance. I'm mindful of the hardware
      beneath and its users. The best solutions in my opinion are those that are built to last,
      minmal, efficient, and even beautiful.
    </p>
    <p>
      I'm one of those lucky people who can make a living out of their hobby. And as any other
      hobby, it's better shared. I enjoy working through hard problems with other passionate people.
      Specially if they are as paranoid with format, simplicity and speed as I am :).
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
